name: Tangela
flavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Tangrowth
flavorText: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it's fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Shuckle
flavorText: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.
Attack1Text: Heal 40 damage from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

name: Cherubi
flavorText: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Carnivine
flavorText: Using its tentacles to lash itself to trees, it lies in wait for prey, luring it close with sweet-smelling drool.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage and discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Snivy
flavorText: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Servine
flavorText: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Serperior
flavorText: They raise their heads to intimidate opponents but only give it their all when fighting a powerful opponent.
Ability1Text: At any time between turns, heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Move as many Grass Energy attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Sewaddle
flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Sewaddle
flavorText: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

name: Swadloon
flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Leavanny
flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached to it has no Weakness.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

name: Crustle
flavorText: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Virizion
flavorText: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Leaf Wallop does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Genesect
flavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
Attack2Text: Does 20 more damage for each Grass Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.
Attack1Text: Attach 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.
Attack2Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Charizard
flavorText: It is said that Charizard's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Vulpix
flavorText: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Ninetales
flavorText: Each of its nine tails is imbued with supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has any basic Energy attached to it that is the same type as the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Moltres
flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, after you flip any coins for an attack, you may ignore all effects of those coin flips and being flipping those coins again. You can't use more than 1 Victory Star Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Move all Energy attached to this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Victini-EX
Attack1Text: Search your deck for 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Pokémon-EX, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Tepig
flavorText: It can deftly dodge its foe's attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Pignite
flavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When it trouble, it emits smoke.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Emboar
flavorText: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Reshiram
flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.
Attack1Text: Does 10 or more for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Reshiram-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 50 damage to itself.

name: Magikarp
flavorText: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Gyarados
flavorText: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the number of Prize cards both players have taken.

name: Articuno
flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Piplup
flavorText: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Prinplup
flavorText: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Empoleon
flavorText: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has fewer remaining HP than the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Phione
flavorText: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.
Attack1Text: Put a card from your discard pile on top of your deck.
Attack2Text: Return this Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

name: Oshawott
flavorText: The scalchop on its stomach is made from the same elements as claws. It detaches the scalchop for use as a blade.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Dewott
flavorText: Scalchop techniques differ from one Dewott to another. It never neglects maintaining its scalchops.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon. This attack does 10 more damage for each heads.

name: Samurott
flavorText: Part of the armor on its anterior legs becomes a giant sword. Its cry alone is enough to intimidate most enemies.
Ability1Text: Any damage done to this Pokémon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Tympole
flavorText: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad
flavorText: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to capture prey.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

name: Seismitoad
flavorText: It increases the power of its punches by vibrating the bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder to rubble with one punch.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

name: Kyurem
flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Kyurem-EX
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't use Hail Blizzard during your next turn.

name: Keldeo-EX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch this Pokémon with your Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Plusle
flavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 4 cards. If Minun is on your Bench, draw 4 more cards.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Minun
flavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 30 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Emolga
flavorText: They live on treetops and glide using the inside of a cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Thundurus
flavorText: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Zekrom
flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 40 damage to itself.

name: Zekrom-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Mewtwo-EX
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Natu
flavorText: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

name: Xatu
flavorText: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.
Attack1Text: You and your opponent play Rock-Paper-Scissors. The player who wins draws 3 cards. The player who loses discards the top 3 cards of his or her deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Misdreavus
flavorText: A Pokémon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

name: Mismagius
flavorText: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Ralts
flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Sableye
flavorText: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: The croaking that Toxicroak produces before a battle is for churning the poison it has stored in its poison sac.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Woobat
flavorText: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for 2 Psychic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Sigilyph
flavorText: The guardians of an ancient city, they use their psychic power to attack enemies that invade their territory.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by Pokémon-EX.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, each Pokémon in play, in each player's hand, and in each player's discard pile has no Abilities (except for Garbotoxin).

name: Gothita
flavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Gothita
flavorText: It stares intently at everything. It can become so obsessed with watching that it doesn't notice attacks.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Gothorita
flavorText: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Gothitelle
flavorText: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Item cards from his or her hand.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Solosis
flavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others

name: Solosis
flavorText: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order.
Attack2Text: Does 40 damage times the number of Reuniclus you have in play.

name: Chandelure-EX
Attack1Text: Put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Confused.

name: Meloetta
flavorText: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Riolu
flavorText: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions such as joy and rage in the form of waves.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Lucario
flavorText: A well-trained one can sense auras to identify and take in the feelings of creatures over half a mile away.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Gallade
flavorText: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it.

name: Excadrill-EX
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your deck. If that card is a basic Energy card, attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon).
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Landorus
flavorText: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Meloetta
flavorText: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Spiritomb
flavorText: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.
Ability1Text: Each player can't play any ACE SPEC cards from his or her hand.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a number of cards equal to the number of cards in your opponent's hand.

name: Darkrai-EX
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokémon that has any Darkness Energy attached to it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Zorua
flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon. (This counts as evolving this Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Zoroark
flavorText: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the number of Darkness Pokémon you have in play.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokémon.

name: Cobalion
flavorText: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.
Attack1Text: Does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Altaria
flavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, discard all Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Rayquaza
flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

name: Gible
flavorText: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

name: Gabite
flavorText: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokémon.

name: Garchomp
flavorText: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Deino
flavorText: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Zweilous
flavorText: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Hydreigon
flavorText: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Darkness Energy attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Black Kyurem-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

name: White Kyurem-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon. The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Lugia-EX
Ability1Text: If your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack of this Pokémon, take 1 more Prize card.
Attack1Text: Discard a Plasma Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you can't discard a Plasma Energy, this attack does nothing.

name: Swablu
flavorText: For some reason, it likes to land on people's heads softly and act like it's a hat.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Minccino
flavorText: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Cinccino
flavorText: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.
Ability1Text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 50 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Druddigon
flavorText: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Bouffalant
flavorText: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
Attack1Text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during his or her last turn, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Tornadus
flavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Move a basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Reshiram
flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Zekrom
flavorText: This Pokémon appears in legends. In its tail, it has a giant generator that creates electricity.
Attack1Text: Does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 40 damage to itself.

name: Snivy
flavorText: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.
Attack1Text: Attach a Grass Energy from your hand to this Pokémon.

name: Servine
flavorText: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Serperior
flavorText: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior's noble eyes.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has any Grass Energy attached to it, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.
Attack1Text: Heal all damage from this Pokémon. This Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Torchic
flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

name: Piplup
flavorText: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Pikachu
flavorText: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Ralts
flavorText: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.
Attack1Text: Draw a card for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Gardevoir
flavorText: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Move all damage counters from this Pokémon to the Defending Pokémon. This Pokémon can't use Eternal Radiance during your next turn.

name: Meloetta-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Does 30 damage times the number of your Pokémon that have the Round attack.

name: Stunfisk

flavorText: Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.

evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.
